---

## Requirements

numpy
scipy
opencv-python
matplotlib
scikit-image
tqdm

Install all dependencies using:
```bash
pip install numpy scipy opencv-python matplotlib scikit-image tqdm
How to Run

Clone the repository and navigate to the project directory.

Install the required Python packages.

Open the Jupyter Notebook project-version2.ipynb.

Set the paths to the content and style images.

Run all notebook cells sequentially to generate the stylized output.

Expected Outputs

The project produces stylized images that preserve the spatial structure of the content image while adopting textures and color distributions from the style image. Output images are saved in the results directory. Intermediate visualizations may also be displayed within the notebook to illustrate the effect of patch size, scale, and iteration count on the final result.

